a day before a north carolina man was scheduled to be executed for a 1987 stabbing the state supreme court postponed the execution because of concerns that gov mike easley the former attorney general might have a conflict of interest in the case the court said it would hear arguments on june 7 on the legality of the governor 's role in deciding whether to grant clemency to robert bacon and other death row inmates because in his previous job mr easley was responsible for arguing against death penalty appeals the issue could also affect more than 100 other death row cases in which mr easley participated david firestone nyt

